Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.72,0:35:30.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,比哈蒙德的整辆捷豹还贵\N{\fs90}cost more than Hammond's entire Jaguar?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.82,0:35:33.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你捷豹多少钱 -差不多\N{\fs90}- How much is your Jag? - About the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.09,0:35:36.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,-捷豹带所有选配 -一共51450英镑\N{\fs90}- What, that Jag with all the extras? - That is ￡51,450.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.33,0:35:40.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,而这辆车有52000英镑的选配件\N{\fs90}And this has got ￡52,000 worth of extras in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.10,0:35:44.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,选配件就比整辆捷豹贵一点点\N{\fs90}It's just a little bit more on extras than the entire Jag.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.44,0:35:46.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很... 值\N{\fs90}It's great... value.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.54,0:35:48.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,-詹姆斯 我能说吗 -说吧\N{\fs90}- Can I just say, James... - Yes, do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.71,0:35:52.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的确很喜欢这车的内饰\N{\fs90}...I do quite like the interior of this car.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.01,0:35:55.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 说真的 我喜欢这绗缝皮革\N{\fs90}No, I do. I'll be honest. I like the quilted leather,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.78,0:35:59.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我喜欢这来自峭壁的木头 所有一切\N{\fs90}I like the wood that comes from a cliff and all of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.62,0:36:02.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这外观 抱歉 实在太丑了\N{\fs90}But the exterior, I'm sorry, it's hideous.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.09,0:36:04.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,-丑 巨丑 -好吧 等一下\N{\fs90}- Ugly. Pig ugly. - Yeah, well, hang on a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.06,0:36:08.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,你还记得吗 在很久之前\N{\fs90}Because, do you remember, and it is a long time ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.39,0:36:10.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,当大陆GT刚发布的时候\N{\fs90}when the Continental GT first came out,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.23,0:36:11.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有人都觉得丑\N{\fs90}we all thought that was hideous...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.50,0:36:13.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的 -现在我们都喜欢它了\N{\fs90}- It was. - ...and now we all love it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.77,0:36:15.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-难得我们统一意见 -是 真的\N{\fs90}- It's one of the few things we agree on. - Yes. Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.80,0:36:17.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我觉得这更像你\N{\fs90}But I think this is more like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.94,0:36:21.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,当我最初遇见你时 我觉得你丑\N{\fs90}When I first met you, I thought you were ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.24,0:36:23.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,而现在 我还是觉得你丑\N{\fs90}And now I still think you're ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.68,0:36:26.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,来自帅气男子的苛刻批评\N{\fs90}A crushing criticism from one so handsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.28,0:36:33.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,-詹姆斯 -什么\N{\fs90}- James? - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.79,0:36:34.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,解开门锁\N{\fs90}Unlock the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.32,0:36:38.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 请开门\N{\fs90}James, please unlock the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.39,0:36:42.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在... 这个地方\N{\fs90}We're in... this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.63,0:36:44.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,在车后座上\N{\fs90}In the back of a car,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.40,0:36:46.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,两个人\N{\fs90}together.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.94,0:36:53.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,叹为观止啊 这些地方\N{\fs90}It is remarkable, isn't it? All those places...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.64,0:36:56.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我确定 所有这些地名都是真的\N{\fs90}I'm sure... All those place names are real.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.28,0:36:58.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是真的 真地名 -是的\N{\fs90}- They are real. Yeah, real places. - They really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.04,0:37:01.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,地名都是真的\N{\fs90}Those place names are real.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.65,0:37:04.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 我们晚点再看那没意义的测试\N{\fs90}Anyway, we'll pick up that pointless test later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.52,0:37:06.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不是没意义的 -它就是\N{\fs90}- It's not pointless! - Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.42,0:37:08.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我已经完美地用内裤理论解释了\N{\fs90}I already explained it perfectly well with the underpants thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.82,0:37:12.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一会儿还会用更多地例子来阐释\N{\fs90}And I shall be explaining using more demonstrations later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.29,0:37:15.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,-噢 好了 -但现在到了\N{\fs90}- Oh, good. - But now it is time
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.13,0:37:17.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,明星脑碰脑环节\N{\fs90}for Celebrity Brain Crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.97,0:37:29.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 我们的嘉宾\N{\fs90}Now, our guest...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.07,0:37:30.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天的嘉宾\N{\fs90}our guest today,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.74,0:37:32.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,他执导了蝙蝠侠 人猿猩球\N{\fs90}he directed Batman, Planet Of The Apes,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.98,0:37:34.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,剪刀手爱德华\N{\fs90}Edward Scissorhands.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.35,0:37:37.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且 在上次水雷事故后\N{\fs90}And, after last week's mine disaster,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.32,0:37:41.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,他决定从水雷下方来演播室\N{\fs90}he's decided to come to the studio underneath the mines
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.62,0:37:43.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,坐的是小型潜水艇\N{\fs90}in a miniature submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.62,0:37:46.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 蒂姆·波顿\N{\fs90}Ladies and gentlemen, Tim Burton!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.79,0:37:51.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是潜水艇 他在那儿\N{\fs90}Here is the submarine. There he is,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.56,0:37:54.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,在水雷下悄悄前进\N{\fs90}sneaking underneath the mines.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.33,0:37:57.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-很明智 -他机智地游过来\N{\fs90}- Clever. - As he heads cleverly towards us.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.34,0:38:00.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他就在外面某处 -就在那儿 太棒了\N{\fs90}- He's out there somewhere. - He's out there somewhere. This is fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.17,0:38:02.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们要跟他聊什么 -太多了\N{\fs90}- What are we gonna talk to him about? - There's so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.68,0:38:05.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你想问他什么 -有关圣诞夜惊魂的\N{\fs90}- What do you want to ask him? -  About The Nightmare Before Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.35,0:38:07.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,我最爱的圣诞电影\N{\fs90}It's my favourite Christmas film.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.41,0:38:10.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,是吗 我想问他和约翰尼德普搭档感觉如何\N{\fs90}Is it? I want to know what it's like to work with Johnny Depp.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.62,0:38:12.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,是啊 要问的太多了\N{\fs90}Yeah, there's a lot to talk to him about.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.99,0:38:15.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 在吗\N{\fs90}Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.12,0:38:18.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,潜水艇的信号中断了\N{\fs90}We've lost the feed somehow from the sub.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.56,0:38:20.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢我的神啊  我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, God Almight... Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.39,0:38:22.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦不\N{\fs90}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.43,0:38:30.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,显然潜水艇遭遇了灾难性的事故\N{\fs90}There's obviously been a catastrophic failure with the submarine.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.54,0:38:33.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不知道什么引起的 -是水怪咬坏了\N{\fs90}- No idea what could have caused it. - The monster's bitten it!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.81,0:38:37.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,第一百次声明了 哈蒙德\N{\fs90}For the hundredth time, Hammond,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.94,0:38:41.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有尼斯湖水怪这种东西\N{\fs90}there is no such thing as the Loch Ness Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.95,0:38:46.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是说他来不了了\N{\fs90}Does that mean he's not coming on, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.39,0:38:49.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长 他的肺被灌满了冰水 已沉入了湖底\N{\fs90}Well, James, his lungs have filled with icy water, he's sunk to the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.96,0:38:53.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的身体被压成了一个乒乓球的大小\N{\fs90}and his body is being compressed to the size of a Ping-Pong ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.43,0:38:54.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他来不了了\N{\fs90}So that is a no.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.93,0:38:58.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,没关系 我们还有个备用计划\N{\fs90}It's OK, though, because we have a back-up plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.20,0:38:59.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们有吗 -是的\N{\fs90}- Do we? - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.03,0:39:02.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看 事情是这样的 这些日子里\N{\fs90}You see, the thing is, these days,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.17,0:39:05.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-现在很多的性能车都有弹射起步 -是的\N{\fs90}- a lot of performance cars have launch control. - Ah, yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.74,0:39:09.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,它生效的方式是你把你的脚同时放在刹车和油门上\N{\fs90}The way it works is you put your foot on the throttle and brake at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.64,0:39:13.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,汽载计算机会精确计算出你需要多少转速\N{\fs90}and the car's computer works out exactly how many revs you need
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.65,0:39:16.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,轮胎应该有多少滑移率\N{\fs90}and exactly how much wheelspin to give the car
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.18,0:39:18.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,从而在你脚离开刹车同时\N{\fs90}so that you get an absolutely perfect start
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.32,0:39:20.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,使你的车完成一个完美的起步\N{\fs90}as soon as you just take your foot off the brake.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.62,0:39:24.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 所以我们在想 这究竟什么时候可以用得上\N{\fs90}Yeah, and we were wondering, just when exactly can you use that?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.09,0:39:26.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你在市中心等红绿灯的时候 让车这样\N{\fs90}If you're in a town centre at a set of lights going...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.83,0:39:30.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,-懂我的意思嘛 -这有一点不文明\N{\fs90}- Know what I mean? - It's a bit rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.43,0:39:33.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 就像这个小视频里所展示的\N{\fs90}It is, as this short film explains.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.28,0:39:51.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,请来一杯椰奶拿铁加焦糖\N{\fs90}Coconut-milk latte with a caramel shot, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.35,0:39:53.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 一杯椰奶拿铁加焦-\N{\fs90}OK, a coconut-milk latte with a caramel--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.59,0:41:05.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,-要这有何用 -没用\N{\fs90}- What is it for? - Pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.83,0:41:09.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,事情是这样的 你不能\N{\fs90}The thing is, you can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.96,0:41:12.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,你甚至都不能在赛道上用弹射起步\N{\fs90}you can't even use launch control on a race track,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.83,0:41:15.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为三四秒钟后 发动机的过热保护就会给发动机断油\N{\fs90}because you can only engage it for three or four seconds before it cuts out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.04,0:41:18.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且你不知道灯什么时候变绿\N{\fs90}And because you don't know when the lights are gonna go green,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.04,0:41:21.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,你就不能准确的开始弹射起步 不是吗\N{\fs90}you don't know when your three seconds start, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.61,0:41:23.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,的确 因为我们认为\N{\fs90}Exactly, which is why we have decided
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.08,0:41:26.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是有史以来最没用的发明\N{\fs90}it is the most pointless invention ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.28,0:41:28.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 说到没有意义\N{\fs90}Yes, and talking of pointless,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.21,0:41:30.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到我们的片子上\N{\fs90}let's get back to our film.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.22,0:41:33.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩 我们对一辆揽胜和其他车做了路测\N{\fs90}Er... We're road-testing a Range Rover and some other cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.92,0:41:37.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,从德国的紫薇村开始\N{\fs90}We began in the German village of Wank,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.36,0:41:40.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,计划穿越亲亲乡和摸摸寨\N{\fs90}and the plan was to go through Kissing and Petting
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.26,0:41:42.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,前往我们的终点领证村\N{\fs90}towards Wedding, which was our destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.93,0:41:47.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我们开始行动并决定留在啪\N{\fs90}Yes, and we pick up the action having decided to spend the night in Fu--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.57,0:41:55.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二天我们在这被露水浸润的小镇醒来\N{\fs90}We woke the next morning in this dew-kissed village.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.91,0:42:00.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,在结束了颇为尴尬的早餐之后\N{\fs90}And over a rather awkward breakfast,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.58,0:42:02.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,大猩猩发布了一段言论\N{\fs90}Clarkson made an announcement.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.99,0:42:10.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不想伤害或不尊重谁\N{\fs90}I don't mean to be hurtful or disrespectful,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.72,0:42:12.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是 恩\N{\fs90}but erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.06,0:42:15.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,-说呀 别吞吞吐吐 -好吧 这\N{\fs90}- Go on, spit it out. - Well, it's...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.60,0:42:17.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,就因为我们住这里\N{\fs90}just because we've been here,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.33,0:42:20.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,并不意味着我们就必须要去领证\N{\fs90}doesn't mean we necessarily have to go on to Wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.63,0:42:21.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,啥\N{\fs90}Aw!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.87,0:42:25.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说的是我 不是你\N{\fs90}It's me, it's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.47,0:42:28.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说的没错 到目前一切都很顺利\N{\fs90}No, he's right. It's been going so well.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.91,0:42:30.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,但如果我们去领证\N{\fs90}And if we go on to Wedding,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.71,0:42:34.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就必须一直保持关系\N{\fs90}we'll have to carry on and on and on,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.31,0:42:37.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,穿过琐事 厌倦\N{\fs90}through Routine, Boredom,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.62,0:42:40.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,怨恨 分床\N{\fs90}Resentment, Spare Bedroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.42,0:42:42.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,诱惑 外遇\N{\fs90}Temptation, Affair,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.45,0:42:45.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,觉悟 悔恨 复仇\N{\fs90}Discovery, Remorse, Revenge,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.79,0:42:48.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,离婚 然后到死亡\N{\fs90}Divorce, and then it's Death.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.23,0:42:51.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者你可以试试摇一摇\N{\fs90}Or you could turn off through Online Dating,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.03,0:42:54.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,随便的约炮 事后无尽的悔恨\N{\fs90}Meaningless Sex, Bottomless Regret,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.67,0:42:57.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,破产 然后心肌梗塞\N{\fs90}Financial Ruination, and then Heart Attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.14,0:42:59.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终又回到死亡\N{\fs90}And then you end up at Death anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.47,0:43:02.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 哈蒙德 这就是为什么我建议\N{\fs90}Exactly, Hammond. And that's why I'm suggesting
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.74,0:43:06.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,与其去领证\N{\fs90}that instead of going to... Wedding,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.11,0:43:07.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们还是去纽博格林吧\N{\fs90}we go to the Nürburgring.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.02,0:43:13.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为船长的车是唯一可以用德语的\N{\fs90}Because James's car was the only one that spoke German,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.89,0:43:15.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他设置了导航\N{\fs90}he set the satnav.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.92,0:43:19.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,输入目的地 纽博格林\N{\fs90}Ziel eingeben: Nürburgring.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.26,0:43:22.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们出发吧\N{\fs90}-  And then we set off.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.37,0:43:31.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 我们来到了Autobahn上\N{\fs90}Soon, we were on Germany's Autobahns,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.67,0:43:36.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,不禁让人思考他们有多明智\N{\fs90}which got us thinking about how sensible they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.74,0:43:39.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们现在在Autobahn上\N{\fs90}And here we are on the Autobahn.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.11,0:43:40.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有限速\N{\fs90}No speed limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.58,0:43:42.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,很混乱吗 并不\N{\fs90}Is it chaos? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.98,0:43:46.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,即使你废除限速\N{\fs90}If you remove the speed limits,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.12,0:43:50.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,人们也不会突然以320kph的时速冲向桥柱\N{\fs90}people don't all suddenly drive into bridge supports at 200 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.89,0:43:55.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们才不傻 这就好比你在野生动物园\N{\fs90}We're not that stupid. Just as if you leave the gate unlocked
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.70,0:43:57.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,把狮子区的门开着\N{\fs90}at the lion closure at a safari park,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.43,0:44:00.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们不会跑进去并在里面开野餐\N{\fs90}we don't all run in and have a picnic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.30,0:44:07.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,在过去的15年里 英国的经济增长了58%\N{\fs90}In the last 15 years, Britain's economy has grown by 58%,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.84,0:44:11.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,而德国增长了102%\N{\fs90}whereas Germany's has grown by 102%.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.44,0:44:16.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是因为我们都开32kph时人家开320kph\N{\fs90}And that's because we're all doing 20 miles an hour and they're doing 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.15,0:44:19.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,速度对商业有益\N{\fs90}Speed is good for business,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.92,0:44:22.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,还能拯救生命\N{\fs90}and it saves lives as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.55,0:44:24.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为当我们行驶在英国的公路上时\N{\fs90}Because when we drive down the motorway in Britain,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.99,0:44:27.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们观察每个台架来看是否有测速相机\N{\fs90}we're looking at all the gantries to see if they have speed cameras,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.83,0:44:32.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者看自己的车速表来确保自己没有超速\N{\fs90}or we're looking at our speedometers to make sure we're not breaking the limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.51,0:44:34.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们没有好好看着路\N{\fs90}We're not looking where we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.40,0:44:38.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,对限速的严格执行会要人命啊\N{\fs90}Heavily enforced speed limits kill people.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.81,0:44:41.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,Autobahn还让我们思考\N{\fs90}The Autobahn also got us thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.61,0:44:45.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,时间是怎么改变了SUV的阵营\N{\fs90}about how times have changed on the SUV front.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.15,0:44:49.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,这真的很惊人 一辆越野车\N{\fs90}It is amazing, really, that an off-road vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.78,0:44:51.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以坐起来如此稳定\N{\fs90}can feel this stable,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.38,0:44:53.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,如此扎实 我想就是这个词\N{\fs90}this planted, I think the word is.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.62,0:44:55.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为在不远的过去\N{\fs90}Because it's not that long ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.39,0:44:57.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你想想早期的揽胜的那个样子\N{\fs90}if you think about early Range Rovers and the like,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.79,0:44:59.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,开快了其实是很吓人的\N{\fs90}going fast was actually quite frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.83,0:45:03.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们的遮阳板上有贴纸 你们记得吗\N{\fs90}They had stickers on the sun visors, do you remember,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.30,0:45:04.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,上面有一个翻车的图片\N{\fs90}with a picture of the car toppling over.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.03,0:45:07.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,禁止急转弯\N{\fs90}"Avoid sudden swerves."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.13,0:45:09.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我完全忘了那个贴纸\N{\fs90}Yes, I'd completely forgotten
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.07,0:45:10.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实你是对的 的确如此\N{\fs90}about that sticker, but you're right, it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.97,0:45:15.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你转动方向盘 这辆车会翻过来\N{\fs90}"If you operate the steering wheel, this vehicle will fall over."
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.64,0:45:19.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,-伙计们 -怎么了\N{\fs90}-  Chaps? -  What?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.78,0:45:21.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里没有限速对吧\N{\fs90}There are no speed limits, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.25,0:45:24.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们可以让我们的车跑到极速\N{\fs90}So we are allowed to go as fast as our cars will go.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.28,0:45:27.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是谁真敢这么做\N{\fs90}But who dares actually do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.12,0:45:29.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁敢跑到极速\N{\fs90}Who dares go the fastest?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.49,0:45:33.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 如果你们想玩的话 我也要掺和了\N{\fs90}Right, if we're going to play that game, I might even join in.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.29,0:45:34.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,好啊\N{\fs90}Bang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.99,0:45:36.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,继续 詹姆斯 你自便\N{\fs90}Go on, James. Help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.30,0:45:43.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,走起 299km/h 极速 -真的?\N{\fs90}- There you go, 187, top speed. -  Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.80,0:45:48.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 你出发的时候就在我后面 现在你还在我后面\N{\fs90}The thing is, you were behind me when you started and you still are behind me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.37,0:45:51.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我的极速是304km/h -哦 我去! 你开不了那么快\N{\fs90}- I did 190. - Oh, for God's sake! You didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.88,0:45:54.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,这比你车的极速要快\N{\fs90}That's faster than your car will go.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.85,0:45:58.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,为了结束这场哔哔\N{\fs90}In order to put a stop to this nonsense,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.62,0:46:01.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,我让大家在下一个服务区停了下来\N{\fs90}I made us pull in at the next service station.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.46,0:46:05.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 小相机\N{\fs90}Right, small cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.16,0:46:07.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们把这个对着仪表盘 这样就能看见仪表盘了\N{\fs90}We fix these to the dash where they can see the speedo,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.29,0:46:09.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以就不会有作弊了\N{\fs90}and then there's no cheating.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.00,0:46:11.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么你牵了只狗\N{\fs90}Why have you got a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.63,0:46:13.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我会告诉你们的 跟我来\N{\fs90}I shall show you. Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.50,0:46:17.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你想要一只宠物\N{\fs90}If you want a pet,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.37,0:46:19.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以买一些贵的\N{\fs90}you can have something expensive,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.17,0:46:21.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如带着银项链的鬣鳞蜥\N{\fs90}like an iguana with a silver necklace.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.14,0:46:23.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者你也可以买一些便宜的 比如蚂蚁\N{\fs90}Or you can have something cheap, like an ant.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.84,0:46:25.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-什么蚂蚁? -那个蚂蚁\N{\fs90}-  What ant? - That ant.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.85,0:46:30.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者靠你的常识 买一只拉布拉多\N{\fs90}Or you can use your common sense and have a labradog.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.12,0:46:40.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我机智的讲解结束之后\N{\fs90}With my clever demonstration over,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.33,0:46:41.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们重回高速\N{\fs90}we got back on the motorway
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.03,0:46:46.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,还装上了哈蒙德的诚实相机\N{\fs90}and mounted Hammond's honesty cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.13,0:46:48.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我还有个作弊的好办法\N{\fs90}I've got a good way of cheating still.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.87,0:46:51.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为如果我按下这个按钮 看好了\N{\fs90}Because if I push this button here, watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.04,0:46:54.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的速度就会变到公里每小时\N{\fs90}my speedometer changes to kilometres an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.97,0:46:56.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,他永远不会知道\N{\fs90}He'll never know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.51,0:46:58.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 你装上相机的时候\N{\fs90}And Jeremy, while you're setting your camera up,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.44,0:47:01.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,别想着把你的显示调到km/h\N{\fs90}don't think about changing your display to km/h
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.61,0:47:03.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以你的数字就会更大了\N{\fs90}so you get a bigger number.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.96,0:47:13.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,验证极速的时刻到了\N{\fs90}It was now time to begin the speed trials.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.90,0:47:21.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,走起 来干票大的\N{\fs90}Here we go. Going for a big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.07,0:47:24.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,进入到一个速度和荣耀的世界\N{\fs90}Into a world of speed and glory!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.64,0:47:28.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油 奥迪 你一定要懂我啊\N{\fs90}Come on, Audi. You must be able to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.07,0:47:30.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油\N{\fs90}Come on, come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.51,0:47:35.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,让开啊 你在一辆奥迪里 加油\N{\fs90}Out of the way. And you in the Audi. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.68,0:47:38.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着交通顺畅起来\N{\fs90}As the traffic eased,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.52,0:47:42.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德叩开了240km/h的大门\N{\fs90}Hammond was knocking on the door of 150 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.62,0:47:45.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是237km/h了\N{\fs90}That's 148.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.03,0:47:47.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,238km/h\N{\fs90}Forty-nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.46,0:47:49.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我 也开始慢慢逼近\N{\fs90}And I, too, was getting close.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.96,0:47:52.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,240km/h快到了了 现在任何时候都可能到240km/h\N{\fs90}150 coming up. 150 any minute now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.76,0:47:57.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油 抓住它\N{\fs90}Come on, stretch it, stretch it, stretch it, stretch it, stretch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.70,0:48:01.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,不幸的是 我们很难知道船长跑了多快\N{\fs90}Sadly, it was hard to say how fast James was going,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.24,0:48:02.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为他是个智障\N{\fs90}because he's an imbecile.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.68,0:48:12.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦耶 那个大数字来了\N{\fs90}Oh, yeah! That big number's coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.62,0:48:15.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,达成挑战242km/h\N{\fs90}Got to beat 151.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.46,0:48:18.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,靠!\N{\fs90}Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.62,0:48:21.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么它就快不过那个速度了?\N{\fs90}Why won't it go any faster than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.43,0:48:23.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊!\N{\fs90}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.60,0:48:26.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,为啥你快不过237km/h?\N{\fs90}Why won't you go any faster than 148?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.64,0:48:39.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终 繁忙的路面终结了这场重要的比赛\N{\fs90}Eventually, heavy traffic ended this important test.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.28,0:48:43.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 鉴于我们身陷堵车之中\N{\fs90}Right, as we are in a traffic jam,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.98,0:48:47.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也该告诉你们谁赢了\N{\fs90}I may as well give you the results of Who Dares Wins.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.05,0:48:51.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德 哈蒙德 250km/h\N{\fs90}Richard Hammond, 155 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.16,0:48:54.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的揽胜最高238km/h\N{\fs90}I maxed the Range Rover at 149.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.29,0:48:57.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,而船长 由于他是个唠叨的白痴\N{\fs90}And James May, because he's a blithering idiot,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.00,0:48:59.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,6000转\N{\fs90}6,000rpm.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.20,0:49:06.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,白痴的车还烧光了油\N{\fs90}The idiot's car had also drained its tank,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.14,0:49:07.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以当他加油的时候\N{\fs90}so while he was filling up,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.77,0:49:11.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,我开始了另一场机智的证明\N{\fs90}I set up another of my clever demonstrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.91,0:49:15.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,先生们 显而易见\N{\fs90}Gentlemen, observe.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.75,0:49:18.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以买非常贵的太阳镜\N{\fs90}You can buy very expensive sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.32,0:49:20.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,这种是用纯金做的\N{\fs90}These ones are made from real gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.49,0:49:22.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者你还可以买非常便宜的太阳镜\N{\fs90}Or you can buy very cheap sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.65,0:49:24.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是应该怎么做呢\N{\fs90}But what do we all do?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.02,0:49:26.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们都买雷朋\N{\fs90}We all have Ray-Bans.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.86,0:49:32.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道你这样让人很不爽吗\N{\fs90}You do know you're just being irritating, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.33,0:49:35.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,一谈到你的车 你只会扯到 内裤\N{\fs90}All you've actually told us about your car is something to do with underpants,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.93,0:49:37.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,鬣鳞蜥和太阳镜\N{\fs90}iguanas and sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.34,0:49:39.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我只是就事论事 -才不是!\N{\fs90}- I'm just saying. - Well, don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.61,0:49:44.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到路上 我们继续跟着詹姆斯\N{\fs90}Back on the move, we continued to follow James
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.61,0:49:47.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,踏上去纽伯格林的旅途\N{\fs90}on our journey to the Nürburgring.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.45,0:49:51.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是过了一会儿 我开始有点担心\N{\fs90}But after a while, I started to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.05,0:49:55.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,他在往哪走?\N{\fs90}Where's he going?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.19,0:49:57.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么我们从高速上下来了?\N{\fs90}Why have we turned off the motorway?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.11,0:50:02.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,您已到达目的地\N{\fs90}Sie haben das Ziel erreicht
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.70,0:50:07.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-詹姆斯... -怎么了?\N{\fs90}- James... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.27,0:50:09.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯 我就直说了吧\N{\fs90}Well, I'm going to get straight to the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.90,0:50:12.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是纽伯格林\N{\fs90}This is not the Nürburgring.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.21,0:50:15.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是纽伦堡\N{\fs90}It's Nuremberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.55,0:50:23.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,-呃 好吧 是的 但是 -没有"呃 好吧"的话\N{\fs90}- Ah, well, yes, but-- - There's no "Ah, well" about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.62,0:50:25.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,是这样 我实际上不会说德语\N{\fs90}The thing is, I can't actually speak German,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.75,0:50:28.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,只会说近朱者赤近墨者黑之类的话\N{\fs90}only the bit about hands being wet because he's under a waterfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.79,0:50:32.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是纽伯格林的英语德语发音是一样的\N{\fs90}But Nürburgring is the same in English as it is in German.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.79,0:50:35.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在我车里用德语和语音控制交流\N{\fs90}I did it with voice control in German with my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.23,0:50:38.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,设置到德国后 我说纽伯格林 它闪了一下\N{\fs90}It was set to German. I said Nürburgring and it went "blink"
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.10,0:50:40.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,-然后我说了"是的" 但是这个名字很相似   -别再责备车了!\N{\fs90}- and I said, "Yes." But it's a similar name. - Don't blame the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.60,0:50:42.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 是我没有准确发音\N{\fs90}Well, I didn't pronounce it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.70,0:50:45.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,你这解释就好像因为我俩名字都是"J"开头所以就容易搞混了\N{\fs90}That's like muddling up our names cos they both begin with J.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.47,0:50:48.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 我们别接着吵了\N{\fs90}Look, let's not get all bogged down
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.07,0:50:49.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,就因为一个大傻X\N{\fs90}with who's been a massive idiot
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.71,0:50:52.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且他说的话起不到任何正面作用\N{\fs90}and despite what he claims can't do anything properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.74,0:50:56.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没用 -我们可以找个附近的赛道代替一下\N{\fs90}- Nothing. - Let's instead look for a race track near here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.32,0:50:58.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,为啥不去试着找一个呢?\N{\fs90}Why don't we try and find one?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.05,0:51:05.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,而这就是哈蒙德找到的赛道\N{\fs90}And that is exactly what Hammond did.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.63,0:51:17.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,在哪?\N{\fs90}Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.40,0:51:19.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯 它就在你们周围 看 我已经标出来了\N{\fs90}Well, it's all around you. Look, I've marked it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.17,0:51:21.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,看 它绕着那 从那上去 沿着那边走\N{\fs90}Look, it goes around there and up there and along there,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.77,0:51:24.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后从那里下去 从那再绕回来\N{\fs90}and then down there and round there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.61,0:51:26.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,这实际上不是个赛道 不是么\N{\fs90}It's not really a track, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.25,0:51:27.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 它更好 这是场拉力赛\N{\fs90}No, it's better. It's rallying.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.81,0:51:31.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是有史以来第一场纽伦堡拉力赛\N{\fs90}This will be the first ever Nuremberg Rally.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.58,0:51:35.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,呃 不是 确实是第一场么\N{\fs90}Well, not the... absolute first ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.89,0:51:37.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说的对\N{\fs90}He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.42,0:51:40.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们想过没 如果我们在这赛车\N{\fs90}Do you imagine, if we did motorcycling round here,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.23,0:51:43.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,这将会是史上第一次纽伦堡审判\N{\fs90}it would be the first ever Nuremberg Trials?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.20,0:51:44.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们可以试一下\N{\fs90}Well, we could give it a go.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.66,0:51:46.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,学会走路之前别跑\N{\fs90}Let's not run before we can walk, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.20,0:51:51.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,由于哈蒙德的路线上布满了扭曲的弯道\N{\fs90}Since Hammond's course featured twisting bends,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.90,0:51:53.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,松散的路面\N{\fs90}loose surfaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.74,0:51:57.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,峭壁 还有成堆的巨石\N{\fs90}sheer drops and piles of enormous rocks everywhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.91,0:52:00.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以练习圈就很必要了\N{\fs90}some practice laps were in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.65,0:52:06.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里要慢因为这块尘土飞扬\N{\fs90}Slightly slow there cos I go round a dusty one,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.82,0:52:09.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后这里是...我也不知道\N{\fs90}and then this is... I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.62,0:52:14.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,"危险" 好吧 我会记住的\N{\fs90}"Danger." Right. I'll take note of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.66,0:52:17.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可不想从这摔下去\N{\fs90}I don't want to fall off there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.86,0:52:20.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我去 我真不想从这摔下去\N{\fs90}Oh, shit. I really don't want to fall off there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.53,0:52:24.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 这块真是很吓人\N{\fs90}Now, this bit is really scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.24,0:52:26.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.51,0:52:28.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,这有点吓尿了的节奏\N{\fs90}That's a bit of a trouser-changer.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.91,0:52:31.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可真是有趣啊\N{\fs90}Ooh! Now, this is quite interesting,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.91,0:52:33.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为在正常情况下\N{\fs90}cos in normal use,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.95,0:52:39.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,这台捷豹所有的动力都被输送到后轮\N{\fs90}all of the power is sent to the rear wheels in the Jag.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.08,0:52:40.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是它能把最多50%的动力\N{\fs90}But it can then send power,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.82,0:52:44.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,输送到前轮\N{\fs90}up to 50% of it, to the front wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.32,0:52:47.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 在这里我稍有疏忽就会酿成大错\N{\fs90}Right, this is where I can go very wrong if I'm not careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.86,0:52:48.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,卧槽\N{\fs90}Oh, shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.70,0:53:00.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,与此同时 大猩猩决定他不需要练习\N{\fs90}Clarkson, meanwhile, had decided he didn't need to have a practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.07,0:53:03.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在干什么?\N{\fs90}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.94,0:53:06.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是等哈蒙德回来之后的豆子演示\N{\fs90}It's my baked beans demonstration for when Hammond gets back.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.81,0:53:09.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为超市有便宜豆子\N{\fs90}Because we've got cheap supermarket beans,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.48,0:53:10.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有贵的...\N{\fs90}then expensive...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.82,0:53:13.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦天 我可没工夫搞这个\N{\fs90}Oh, God. I haven't got time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.39,0:53:16.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后 中间是揽胜...\N{\fs90}And then, in the middle, the Range Rover...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.29,0:53:17.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦!\N{\fs90}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.26,0:53:22.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着练习结束\N{\fs90}With practice over,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.16,0:53:25.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德准备开始跑计时圈\N{\fs90}Hammond lined up on the beginning line for his timed lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.83,0:53:30.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德·哈蒙德 准备出发 三 二 一\N{\fs90}Richard Hammond, begin in three, two, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.17,0:53:31.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,走！\N{\fs90}Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.87,0:53:35.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,走起\N{\fs90}Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.41,0:53:38.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊 哈蒙德 集中注意力\N{\fs90}Now, come on, Hammond. Concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.31,0:53:46.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦! 漂亮的飞跃漂移\N{\fs90}Oh! That was beautiful lift-off oversteer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.42,0:53:53.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,稍带刹车 然后...\N{\fs90}A little bit of a brake, and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.70,0:53:58.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦! 这里太快了\N{\fs90}Ooh! That's too fast there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.13,0:54:02.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有点吓尿了\N{\fs90}I just had a wee.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.13,0:54:06.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 我们预测一下他会说啥\N{\fs90}Right, let's predict what he's saying in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.71,0:54:11.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,他会说牵引力控制系统不能真正关闭\N{\fs90}He'll say the traction control won't be turned off properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.08,0:54:13.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为牵引力控制没法完全关闭\N{\fs90}Cos you can't turn the traction control off completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.05,0:54:17.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,他会说 "我需要动力但是不够"\N{\fs90}He'll say, "I need power and there isn't any!"
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.42,0:54:19.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊 动力都去哪了\N{\fs90}Come on! Where's the power?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.65,0:54:21.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,给我动力啊\N{\fs90}Give me power! Give me power!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.05,0:54:25.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 这个... 卧槽\N{\fs90}Now, this one... Oh, shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.76,0:54:30.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这确实有点快了\N{\fs90}This is the really fast bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.13,0:54:35.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊 宝贝! 加油 这就对了 给我动力\N{\fs90}Come on, baby! Come on. That's it. Give me power.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.70,0:54:39.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,高速进入直道\N{\fs90}Going in with big speed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.57,0:54:42.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 提前刹车\N{\fs90}Now, brake early, early, early, early, early,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.04,0:54:44.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后转进去\N{\fs90}and then turn in.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.21,0:54:49.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,搞定\N{\fs90}Bury it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.85,0:54:56.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我会快他十万八千里\N{\fs90}I'm gonna be miles faster than him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.99,0:54:58.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 可你都没有练习过\N{\fs90}Well, you haven't even done any practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.59,0:55:00.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我知道 -说实话没那么容易\N{\fs90}- I know. - It's honestly not that simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.22,0:55:01.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错 是这样\N{\fs90}Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.26,0:55:06.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊!\N{\fs90}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.07,0:55:11.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,尽她所能 就是这样 走起\N{\fs90}Giving it all she can. That's it, there you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.44,0:55:13.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,小小地爆发 然后冲线\N{\fs90}Little burst and across the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.58,0:55:19.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,5分56秒整\N{\fs90}Five minutes 56 dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.41,0:55:21.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,-很好吗 -我不知道\N{\fs90}- That good? - I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.15,0:55:23.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,-5分56 -整\N{\fs90}- Five 56. - Dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.72,0:55:27.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 或者 不 你们看到最后一段路了吗\N{\fs90}Yes! Or no! Did you see me at that last bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.42,0:55:30.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,牵引力控制让我无法释放所有马力\N{\fs90}The traction control just wouldn't let me put the power down there at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.69,0:55:33.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,还停下了 你们看见我停下了吗\N{\fs90}It stopped! Did you see me stop there?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.96,0:55:38.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你为啥拿了个秒表？-给他计时\N{\fs90}- Why have you got a stopwatch? - To time him.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.16,0:55:39.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,不不 看\N{\fs90}No, no, no, no. Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.90,0:55:42.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,-今天几号 4月26号 -好的 知道了\N{\fs90}- What date is it? April 26th. - Oh, yeah. Yeah, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.77,0:55:44.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,-4月26号... -不 一个更好的主意\N{\fs90}- April 26th at... - No, a better idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.00,0:55:48.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们为什么不每天在这顶上计日子呢\N{\fs90}Why don't we just chalk marks on the roof for every day?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.11,0:55:50.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,-每次太阳升起来的时候 记一个 -好\N{\fs90}- Every time the sun comes up, OK, another mark. - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.61,0:55:53.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 梅 你可以出发了\N{\fs90}James May, you may begin
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.65,0:55:56.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,三 二 一\N{\fs90}in three, two, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.42,0:55:58.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,出发\N{\fs90}Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.45,0:56:03.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长为了英国和德国驾驶宾利出发了!\N{\fs90}And May is off for Great Britain and Germany in the Bentley!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.22,0:56:05.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他不喜欢高 -不 他不喜欢高\N{\fs90}- He doesn't like heights. - No, he doesn't like heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.52,0:56:07.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他不喜欢速度 -或者滑滑的东西\N{\fs90}- He doesn't like speed. - Or slippery stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.86,0:56:13.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以...所有他讨厌的东西\N{\fs90}So... everything he hates.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.06,0:56:15.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,尽管环境险恶\N{\fs90}Despite the hostile environment,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.70,0:56:17.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,我决心掘地三尺\N{\fs90}I was determined to dig deep
Dialogue: 0,0:56:17.14,0:56:19.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,来彰显宾利的荣耀\N{\fs90}for the honour of the Bentley badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.04,0:56:24.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,好滑\N{\fs90}Slidey, slidey, slidey.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.18,0:56:28.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 碎石路面\N{\fs90}Yes, Tarmac.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.62,0:56:33.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,你... 你听见了吗?\N{\fs90}Did you... Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.72,0:56:37.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是来自船长的响胎\N{\fs90}That was tyre squeal from James May.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.56,0:56:41.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,上坡\N{\fs90}Up the ridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.09,0:56:44.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,降一档\N{\fs90}Knock it down a cog.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.30,0:56:46.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 我天\N{\fs90}Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.80,0:56:48.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,天哪!\N{\fs90}Blimey!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.03,0:56:51.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是船长风格啊 不是么?\N{\fs90}That wasn't very James May-ish, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.84,0:56:53.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,他这样会把自己吓死的\N{\fs90}He'll have frightened himself to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.74,0:56:56.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,刚那段有点疯狂\N{\fs90}That's the dippy bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.28,0:56:59.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看这个\N{\fs90}Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.29,0:57:11.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 他腾空了 他居然腾空了\N{\fs90}Oh! He got air! He got air!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.82,0:57:13.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得他是一心想赢啊\N{\fs90}I think he's being committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.23,0:57:17.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 如果他赢我了怎么办\N{\fs90}Jeremy, what if he beats me?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.73,0:57:19.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,-要是他比你快  -是啊\N{\fs90}- What if he beats you? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.60,0:57:23.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你会蒙羞致死 我将狂笑不止  -嗯 好吧\N{\fs90}- You'll die of shame and I'll die laughing. - Yeah, OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.50,0:57:29.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,即便他如此努力 这老妇人在弯道还是丢了时间\N{\fs90}Try as he might, though, the old lady was losing time in the corners.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.51,0:57:33.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 这车有两吨半重 还很长\N{\fs90}The trouble is, it is a two-and-a-half-tonne fairly long car,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.91,0:57:36.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你没法改变物理定律\N{\fs90}and you can't change the laws of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.62,0:57:39.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,天哪 这可不妙\N{\fs90}Cor! That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.55,0:57:45.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 把它摆正 加油啊\N{\fs90}Oh, get it straight! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.26,0:57:48.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 不 我过头了\N{\fs90}Oh, no! I overdid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.93,0:57:57.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,6分16秒\N{\fs90}Six minutes 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.14,0:57:58.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 他慢16\N{\fs90}So he was 16...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.84,0:58:03.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,18秒 但是他的车卖一百八十多万\N{\fs90}18 seconds slower than you and his car is £212,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.68,0:58:05.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,多吐槽些 写下来\N{\fs90}Say some more of that stuff. Write it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.61,0:58:10.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,终于轮到这里最好的车了\N{\fs90}Finally, it was the turn of the best car here.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.12,0:58:14.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,3 2 1\N{\fs90}Three, two, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.45,0:58:15.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始\N{\fs90}Begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.92,0:58:21.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,他连一个练习圈都没跑过\N{\fs90}He hasn't... done a single practice lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.63,0:58:24.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是说 一次都没有\N{\fs90}I mean, not one.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.73,0:58:27.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,牵引力控制关闭 这就好多了\N{\fs90}Traction control off. That's better.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.57,0:58:30.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,看好了\N{\fs90}And watch this!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.30,0:58:34.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,切进弯 很好地完成\N{\fs90}Flick it in. Nicely done.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.41,0:58:35.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,再往另外一边切出去\N{\fs90}Flick it back the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.58,0:58:40.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,他开车的时候会是什么状态 谦逊\N{\fs90}While he's driving, what do we think he's being? Modest?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.48,0:58:42.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,谦卑  安静\N{\fs90}Self-effacing? Quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.58,0:58:45.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,他可能什么都不说 他应该在专注中\N{\fs90}He probably isn't saying anything. He's probably concentrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.25,0:58:47.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,好棒\N{\fs90}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.79,0:58:51.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 天啊 我样样都行\N{\fs90}Oh, God, I'm good at everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.72,0:58:53.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而 为了赢得这场比赛\N{\fs90}However, in order to win this contest,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.06,0:59:00.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,我并不打算只靠我高超的驾驶技巧\N{\fs90}I had no intention of relying only on my supreme skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.46,0:59:05.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,事情是这样 捷豹和宾利都是公路车\N{\fs90}You see, the thing is, the Jaguar and the Bentley were designed as road cars
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.00,0:59:09.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,再给他们一点越野能力\N{\fs90}and then given some off-road ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.44,0:59:12.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,然而揽胜从设计伊始就是一台越野车\N{\fs90}Whereas the Range Rover was designed as an off-road car,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.01,0:59:16.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,后来又增强了它的路面性能\N{\fs90}and then given some ability to work on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.68,0:59:18.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,这只是细微的区别\N{\fs90}It's only a subtle difference,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.35,0:59:22.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这意味着我不用按照常规\N{\fs90}but it means I don't have to follow the beaten track.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.62,0:59:25.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能抄个近道\N{\fs90}I can take shortcuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.23,0:59:34.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车非常聪明\N{\fs90}It's such a clever car, it really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.97,0:59:41.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能感知到它正在驶过的地形\N{\fs90}This car senses what sort of terrain it's driving over,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.27,0:59:47.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,以此来决定差速锁是锁止还是打开\N{\fs90}and then engages or disengages the differentials accordingly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.35,0:59:51.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,开宾利或者捷豹可来不了这里\N{\fs90}You could not come up here in the Bentley or the Jaguar.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.12,0:59:56.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好安静啊 我听不到 -他此刻在干嘛\N{\fs90}- It's quiet. I can't hear it. - What's he in at the moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.92,0:59:59.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,一条裤子 几罐豆子 拉布拉多\N{\fs90}A pair of pants? Tin of beans? Labrador?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.56,1:00:01.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,还会有更蠢的\N{\fs90}There'll be another stupid...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.36,1:00:04.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的这些都是大路货 我的才是最好的\N{\fs90}"You get ordinary ones and mine's just the best."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.13,1:00:10.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,揽胜的涉水深度\N{\fs90}The Range Rover can wade through water
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.30,1:00:11.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,将近一米深\N{\fs90}nearly a metre deep.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.37,1:00:15.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看啊\N{\fs90}And look at it!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.84,1:00:17.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,多好的一辆车啊\N{\fs90}What a machine you are!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.24,1:00:21.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 我就要速速窜上山了\N{\fs90}Now we just pump back up the hill.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.48,1:00:23.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,马力\N{\fs90}Power!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.75,1:00:25.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,马力啊\N{\fs90}Power now!
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.75,1:00:27.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他在那里   -哎\N{\fs90}- There he is. - Hey?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.79,1:00:29.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不对 等等  -是的 你看 他在那里\N{\fs90}- No, hang on a minute. - No, he's there, look.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.65,1:00:31.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是啊 但是  -咋了\N{\fs90}- No, but... - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.36,1:00:35.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,冲线\N{\fs90}And across the line.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.03,1:00:40.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,他几乎比你快两分钟\N{\fs90}He's almost two minutes quicker than you were.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.90,1:00:42.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不可能\N{\fs90}That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.90,1:00:47.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你是怎么做到的 -啥玩意儿\N{\fs90}- How did you do that? - What?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.61,1:00:50.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这个 -你的车全湿了 本不该如此\N{\fs90}- That. - A, your car's all wet, which it shouldn't be.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.91,1:00:53.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,此外你几乎比哈蒙德快了两分钟\N{\fs90}And you're almost two minutes faster than Hammond.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.58,1:00:55.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 但是 你看 事情是这样的\N{\fs90}Yes, but, you see, the thing is,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.55,1:00:58.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能买一台便宜的车 比如说捷豹\N{\fs90}you can buy a cheap car, like a Jaguar,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.18,1:01:00.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者你能买一台贵的车\N{\fs90}or you can buy an expensive car,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.42,1:01:01.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像宾\N{\fs90}like a Bent--
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.89,1:01:08.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,作弊 作弊 他就是在作弊\N{\fs90}Cheat! Cheat! He just cheated.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.76,1:01:10.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,浪费时间 这整部片子\N{\fs90}A total waste of time, that whole film.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.56,1:01:13.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,完全浪费时间 揽胜 快了两分钟\N{\fs90}A total waste of time. Range Rover, two minutes faster.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.43,1:01:15.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,一句话 你作弊了\N{\fs90}You cheated, simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.37,1:01:19.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,那啥 你看 如果我们把这个争论先放一放\N{\fs90}Anyway, look, if we can just put the bickering aside for one moment,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.10,1:01:20.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不得不说 这个小捷豹\N{\fs90}I have to say, that little Jag was,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.74,1:01:23.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的很棒 它的设计师\N{\fs90}and it really was, brilliant. And it was designed
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.84,1:01:27.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,是一个本地的小伙子 叫Ian Callum 生于邓弗里斯\N{\fs90}by a local boy, Ian Callum, born in Dumfries.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:27.11,1:01:30.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,除此之外 他也设计了阿斯顿马丁DB7\N{\fs90}He didn't just do that. He also styled the Aston Martin DB7,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.75,1:01:33.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,DB9 Vanquish 和 福特Puma\N{\fs90}the DB9, the Vanquish, the Ford Puma,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.45,1:01:35.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有 考斯沃斯版本的Escort\N{\fs90}the Escort Cosworth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.25,1:01:37.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,-于是 他是不列颠人 -基本上是的\N{\fs90}- Yeah, he's British. - Basically, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.12,1:01:38.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 几乎如此\N{\fs90}Well, pretty much.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.56,1:01:40.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,确实 确实\N{\fs90}He is. He is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.39,1:01:43.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是 不幸的是 他的新车没有揽胜好\N{\fs90}Anyway, sadly, his new car isn't as good as a Range Rover.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.83,1:01:45.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,别和我争 它不行\N{\fs90}Don't argue. It isn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.66,1:01:48.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,带着对他彻彻底底的失望 是时候结束了\N{\fs90}And on that terrible disappointment for him, it's time to end.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.87,1:01:50.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢收看\N{\fs90}Thank you so much for watching.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.20,1:01:52.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢你们的到来\N{\fs90}Thank you all so much for coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.00,1:01:54.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们下次再会  再见\N{\fs90}We'll see you next time. Goodbye.
